reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Really like this shelf.Love the way the shelf looks. It was packaged really well, came in two days earlier than expected, the instructions were very straight forward, and all the parts were clearly labeled. It came with two spare parts of each of the hardware and a decent magnetic screwdriver which is quite nice. It definitely needs to be anchored in which I haven't had the chance to do yet, it's a bit wobbly (but I also have carpet and funky floors so that's not the shelves fault).One thing I noticed that I didn't *love* were the dowels- the dowels are kind of thin and short compared the holes they were going into.I'd buy it again!Also- if you bought more than one you could connect them with the metal cross pieces in the back which would be pretty rad.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very strong and sturdy with six adjustable feet.
reviews.reviewText: Pros: Easy to assemble by following picture instructions. Looks even better in person. Was absolutely amazed how the box was packed. I thought there is no way this big of a product fit into such a thin box. The box is heavy and tall so if you are smaller perhaps arrange for someone to be there to help lift it.Cons: Assembly space was required to be at least twice the width of the entire shelf to slide in the individual shelves. I’m really just nitpicking at this point.My only gripe is every single piece of wood had a sticker on it to show what part it is. Great idea except they were hard to remove and left a sticky residue on the wood. That’s like 32 stickers. I need to find a product that will eliminate the stickiness without damaging the wood’s finish.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks great! Nothing broken
reviews.reviewText: I was afraid when I saw the box that it for sure would have broken pieces. The box was smashed, crushed, torn, taped back up and was barely holding together. But NOTHING INSIDE WAS BROKEN!!! They sure know how to pack them, I guess! It was prettier than I thought it’d be. Very rustic industrial vibe. It was super easy to put together but took quite awhile with just one person. I think it’s fairly sturdy. Big bolts, heavy duty metal, lots of screws per shelf. I’m using it for games in the dining room on half, at least. Fits most great with the wider shelves than many. It’s a lot of space and looks great for the $200 price tag.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice shelf. not perfect though
reviews.reviewText: I've been wanting to upgrade the cheap particle board shelves I have. They always claim to support "X" number of pounds, but they NEVER do. When you put the books on them, they always slowly begin to sag or bend in the middle. And real, solid wood shelves cost significantly more.These have the metal braces that the shelves sit on. So, no sagging and capable of supporting weight.They are solid looking shelves, but I had to "upgrade" them to my standards. Modifying them a bit made them almost perfect for me. And they look so much better.As has been mentioned, the sideboard is only about two inches. Not much side support for books that are much taller. Someone mentioned using book ends. That eliminates shelf space. I got 1/2 by 1/2-inch dowel rods, matched them to the length of the sideboard, glued them together, and built up the height of the sideboards on the shelves along the metal sides. And stained them to match. (The sideboards are 1/2 inch wide; the dowel rod is perfectly sized). So now the side boards can support the sides of the books.I also had to stain the edges of the original board pieces. The edges showed the white of the particle board. The original finish did not cover the edge. This was my biggest disappointment in the shelf. That white edge looked cheap and crappy. But once I used a small art brush to stain the white edge, you could not tell.Saying that I had to put in work to make the shelf meet my standard, I am buying another. I like matching shelves, not have an oddball assortment. It will look good once I've modified it for what I want.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid, good looking shelf
reviews.reviewText: I got two of these to accommodate my ever expanding book collection.First thing to note. These are some heavy motherlickers. Almost 100 lbs each. You're probably going to want help bringing them inside.Assembly was pretty straight-forward. Directions were clear. A little time consuming, about an hour per unit to assemble. I would highly recommend completing the frame assembly before tightening any of the screws completely to give yourself a little wiggle room when trying to get everything to fit together.Once assembled, they're very sturdy and very attractive. A little on the pricey side for my taste, but probably worth it as I expect they're going to last a long time.

reviews.reviewTitle: Very happy with my purchase, exactly what I had in mind
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a bookcase wall to fill a room and put books and stuff so I purchased two (2), and these are just perfect, very beautiful, sturdy, very well built.Before purchasing, I read the comments on Amazon and people were talking about having the proper tools so, I was prepared!There are A LOT of screws and although the kits comes with neat tools, it's an insane amount of work to do all manually! If you are prepared with a proper electric drill, it's just perfect, no issues at all.Kits come with spare screws, tools, build instructions and it is very easy to follow. It is also very well packaged with a safe amount of padding. One of the box arrived a bit smashed and I was worried, but everything was perfect inside, nothing bent or broken, super packaging!I'm very happy with my purchase !!! Exactly what I wanted.
